    <svcsubproc>
        <title>Roof Mounted Escape Hatch</title>
        <para>The roof mounted escape hatch allows egress from the bus body through the roof section in the event of an
            emergency where exiting the emergency exit doors or windows is not possible (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f4700421">Fig. 21, Item 3</hotlnk>).
        </para>
        <figure id="f4700421" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg47/G4700421.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                     scalefitheight="272px"/>
            <caption>Figure 21. Roof Emergency Escape Hatch</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. STATIC ROOF VENT (OPTIONAL )</callout1>
                <callout1>2. EXTERNAL HATCH LATCH</callout1>
                <callout1>3. ESCAPE HATCH</callout1>
                <callout1>4. MOUNTING RIVETS WITH CAPS (AROUND PERIMETER)</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
    </svcsubproc>
